#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:4
msgid "CI Pipelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:7
msgid "Rationale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:9
msgid ""
"The goal of testing in a CI pipeline is different from testing locally. "
"Indeed, you can quickly edit some code and run your tests again on your "
"computer, but it is not possible with CI pipeline. They run on a separate "
"server and are triggered by specific actions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:14
msgid ""
"From that observation, pytest can detect when it is in a CI environment and "
"adapt some of its behaviours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:18
msgid "How CI is detected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:20
msgid ""
"Pytest knows it is in a CI environment when either one of these environment "
"variables are set to a non-empty value:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:22
msgid "`CI`: used by many CI systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:23
msgid "`BUILD_NUMBER`: used by Jenkins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:26
msgid "Effects on CI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:28
msgid ""
"For now, the effects on pytest of being in a CI environment are limited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:30
msgid ""
"When a CI environment is detected, the output of the short test summary info "
"is no longer truncated to the terminal size i.e. the entire message will be "
"shown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:32
msgid ""
"# content of test_ci.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_db_initialized():\n"
"    pytest.fail(\n"
"        \"deliberately failing for demo purpose, Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, "
"\"\n"
"        \"consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras facilisis, massa in suscipit \"\n"
"        \"dignissim, mauris lacus molestie nisi, quis varius metus nulla ut "
"ipsum.\"\n"
"    )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:46
msgid "Running this locally, without any extra options, will output:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:48
msgid ""
"$ pytest test_ci.py\n"
"...\n"
"========================= short test summary info "
"==========================\n"
"FAILED test_backends.py::test_db_initialized[d2] - Failed: deliberately f..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:55
msgid "*(Note the truncated text)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:58
msgid "While running this on CI will output:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/explanation/ci.rst:60
msgid ""
"$ export CI=true\n"
"$ pytest test_ci.py\n"
"...\n"
"========================= short test summary info "
"==========================\n"
"FAILED test_backends.py::test_db_initialized[d2] - Failed: deliberately "
"failing\n"
"for demo purpose, Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. "
"Cras\n"
"facilisis, massa in suscipit dignissim, mauris lacus molestie nisi, quis "
"varius\n"
"metus nulla ut ipsum."
msgstr ""
